Thanks for the up,  A/V 7/7

Well the actor is indescript as to heritage. This is nothing like the old "GOOD" Sinbad movies from Ray Harryhausen / Charles Schneer, where Sinbad was clearly arabian, or at least intended to be.

This is actually more along the lines of the very bad TV series. It borrows from every other adventure movie indescriminantly and executes it all poorly. The TV series actually has moments of special effects that where better than ones seen in this flick. It's essentially the junk food of movies and a little sub-par of what the SyFy channel seems to be churning out these days, so brace yourself.

I did manage to watch the entire thing, but maybe that says more about me than the movie.

Just to clarify,  I don't think SyFy channel had anything to do with this movies, just that this movie is actually worse than the majority of the garbage the SyFy channel is making these days.  The release company involved is "the asylum" thier IMDB link pretty much spells out what to expect.
